scheduling DiagnosticChanged seems like a workaround, can/do we need to fix this in ui2? https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/7662001c482d63e1119aafcebc0e13d1201a2805/runtime/lua/vim/_core/ui2.lua#L105 @luukvbaal 

did `nvim_buf_is_valid(buf)` return true for a buffer that is closing, maybe it shouldn't?

```diff
diff --git i/src/nvim/api/buffer.c w/src/nvim/api/buffer.c
index 44604b205bca..793c925418f7 100644
--- i/src/nvim/api/buffer.c
+++ w/src/nvim/api/buffer.c
@@ -1064,7 +1064,8 @@ Boolean nvim_buf_is_valid(Buffer buf)
   FUNC_API_SINCE(1)
 {
   Error stub = ERROR_INIT;
-  Boolean ret = find_buffer_by_handle(buf, &stub) != NULL;
+  buf_T * b = find_buffer_by_handle(buf, &stub);
+  Boolean ret = b != NULL && !!b->b_locked_split;
   api_clear_error(&stub);
   return ret;
 }
```

that will probably break stuff, maybe we need:

    nvim_buf_is_valid(buf, {check_closing=true})

or maybe `scheduled_ui_callback` should have been called instead of `ui_callback` ?

https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/7662001c482d63e1119aafcebc0e13d1201a2805/runtime/lua/vim/_core/ui2.lua#L207-L210
